After 4 years of the trade war with China, the U.S. gained nothing but embarrassment. The U.S. has not only failed to curb China's economic and trade development, but also failed to reduce the trade deficit with China, and bring manufacturing back to the US. Ironically, U.S. politicians realized, that the only way to solve its domestic economic crisis is to rely on China. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Kate Kuiexplains America's failure in the trade war.